1. Instll Python in Windows
2. Create a virtualenv with Python
3. Activate the virtualenv and install the dependecies listed in requirements.txt via pip
4. Edit your PowerBI Desktop options and point the Python interpreter to the "Scripts" folder in your virtualenv path
5. Edit the PowerBI Python script so you have the right accounturl, username and password set for the DB connection to Snowflake
6. Start PowerBI and choose source "Python Script" and copy and paste the whole Python script in the window
7. It may take a bit, wait until there are no more "dots" moving that indicate that PowerBI is still loading the data 
8. When finished you can see the data under "Python --> DF" and import it into a data set.
9. This method does not support Direct Query
